description: The NVIDIA PhysX SDK is a scalable multi-platform physics solution supporting a wide range of devices, from smartphones to high-end multicore CPUs and GPUs. PhysX is already integrated into some of the most popular game engines, including Unreal Engine, and Unity3D.
releaseNotes: Matches the November 4, 2022 release on GitHub.
summary: The NVIDIA PhysX SDK built with vcpkg and VS 2019 for the platforms x86-Windows, x64-Windows, x86-UWP, x64-UWP, ARM64-UWP.
title: PhysX SDK
